npm

definitive, ch.17.4

- keeps track of dependencies in package.json
- by default, node installation includes npm-package manager
- dependencies are stored in node_modules/
    - dev dependency: for dev-tools (not to run the code)
- commands/flags, e.g.
    - 'npm init' creates package.json
    - 'npm install' downloads and installs all declared dependencies in package.json
    - 'npx <tool>' runs locally installed tools, e.g. npx eslint or npx jest
    - -g: global

- SEE ALSO
    - search packages: npmjs.com
